===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An area of a [[mechanical]] [[device]] containing a number of [[key]]s that can be [[press]]ed to generate a controlled response or action, such as on a [[typewriter]] or a [[piano]].
# {{computing}} An electromechanical device with keys affixed to a base used to enter information and interact with an [[electronic]] [[instrument]], [[electric]] [[typewriter]] or [[computer]] using electrical [[signal]]s.
# {{musici}} A component of many [[instruments]] including the [[piano]], [[organ]], and [[harpsichord]] consisting of usually black and white keys that cause different tones to be produced when struck.
# {{music}} A device with keys of a musical keyboard, used to control [[electronic]] sound-producing devices or [[instruments]] which may be built into or separate from the keyboard device.

